.TH "MARATHON" "1" "April 2026" "python\-marathon" "Marathon Exercise Runner"
.SH NAME
marathon \- Python interview prep exercise runner (25 subcommands)
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]python marathon.py\f[R] \f[I]command\f[R] [\f[I]options\f[R]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Marathon is a rustlings\-for\-python style exercise runner for Python
interview prep.
It wraps pytest with progress tracking, SM\-2 spaced repetition, badge
achievements, multi\-user answer sharing, and Exercism exercise
importing.
.PP
Exercises live in numbered directories under tier folders.
Each exercise has a stub (\f[I]problem.py\f[R]), tests
(\f[I]test_problem.py\f[R]), and reference solution
(\f[I].meta/solution.py\f[R]).
The learner edits \f[I]problem.py\f[R] until the tests pass.
.SH CORE WORKFLOW
.TP
\f[B]status\f[R]
Show per\-tier progress, XP level, streak count, earned badges, and a
12\-week activity heatmap.
.TP
\f[B]next\f[R]
Find and run the next unsolved exercise.
.TP
\f[B]run\f[R] \f[I]NNN\f[R] [\f[B]\[en]current\f[R]]
Run pytest on exercise \f[I]NNN\f[R].
Use \f[B]\[en]current\f[R] to rerun the last exercise.
Supports 2D addressing: \f[CR]run \[dq]tier2 3\[dq]\f[R] runs the 3rd
tier2 exercise.
.TP
\f[B]list\f[R] [\f[B]\[en]tier\f[R] \f[I]N\f[R]]
List all exercises with tier, status, and name.
Filter by tier number.
.TP
\f[B]watch\f[R] [\f[I]NNN\f[R]]
Watch \f[I]problem.py\f[R] for changes and rerun tests automatically.
Polls every second.
.TP
\f[B]challenge\f[R] [\f[B]\[en]tier\f[R] \f[I]N\f[R]]
Pick a random unsolved exercise, optionally filtered by tier.
.TP
\f[B]kata\f[R] \f[I]NNN\f[R]
Re\-solve an exercise from scratch.
Backs up current solution, restores the stub, and tracks repetition
count.
.SH HINTS AND SOLUTIONS
.TP
\f[B]hint\f[R] \f[I]NNN\f[R] \f[B]\[en]level\f[R] \f[I]N\f[R]
Show hint at level 1\-3 for exercise \f[I]NNN\f[R].
Records usage in progress.
.TP
\f[B]reveal\f[R] \f[I]NNN\f[R]
Print the reference solution.
Requires typing \f[CR]REVEAL NNN\f[R] to confirm.
.TP
\f[B]reset\f[R] \f[I]NNN\f[R]
Restore \f[I]problem.py\f[R] to its original stub and clear progress.
.SH COLLABORATION
.TP
\f[B]submit\f[R] \f[I]NNN\f[R] [\f[B]\[en]git\f[R]]
Copy your passing \f[I]problem.py\f[R] to
\f[I]answers//NNN/solution.py\f[R].
With \f[B]\[en]git\f[R], also runs \f[I]git add\f[R] and \f[I]git
commit\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]peer\f[R] \f[I]NNN\f[R] \f[B]\[en]user\f[R] \f[I]NAME\f[R]
View another user\[cq]s submitted answer.
Gated: you must have solved the exercise yourself first.
.TP
\f[B]challenge\-peer\f[R] \f[I]NNN\f[R] \f[B]\[en]user\f[R] \f[I]NAME\f[R]
Create a timed challenge with a peer.
Stored in \f[I]answers/challenges.json\f[R].
.SH DISCOVERY AND REVIEW
.TP
\f[B]tag\f[R] [\f[B]\[en]filter\f[R] \f[I]TOPIC\f[R]]
Without \f[B]\[en]filter\f[R]: list all tags with exercise counts.
With \f[B]\[en]filter\f[R]: show exercises matching the topic tag.
.TP
\f[B]recommend\f[R]
Suggest next exercises based on tag coverage (most new tags first).
.TP
\f[B]review\f[R]
SM\-2 spaced repetition queue.
Shows exercises due for review with easiness factors and overdue status.
.TP
\f[B]badges\f[R]
Show all earned and available badges with descriptions.
.SH EXPORT AND IMPORT
.TP
\f[B]export\f[R]
Dump progress JSON to stdout for backup or cross\-machine sync.
.TP
\f[B]import\-progress\f[R] \f[I]FILE\f[R]
Merge progress from a JSON file.
Takes max status, unions badges, preserves SR fields.
.TP
\f[B]export\-obsidian\f[R] \f[B]\[en]vault\f[R] \f[I]PATH\f[R]
Export solved exercises to an Obsidian vault as markdown notes with YAML
frontmatter.
.SH ADMIN
.TP
\f[B]verify\f[R]
Run all reference solutions against their tests silently.
Reports pass/fail summary.
Does not modify learner progress.
.TP
\f[B]lint\-exercises\f[R]
Validate all exercises have the required 7\-file layout, correct test
imports, and stub content.
.TP
\f[B]new\f[R] \f[B]\[en]name\f[R] \f[I]SLUG\f[R] [\f[B]\[en]tier\f[R] \f[I]T\f[R]] [\f[B]\[en]tags\f[R] \f[I]T1,T2\f[R]] [\f[B]\[en]target\-minutes\f[R] \f[I]N\f[R]]
Scaffold a new exercise directory with all 7 files and add a manifest
entry.
.TP
\f[B]import\f[R] \f[B]\[en]slugs\f[R] \f[I]S\f[R] [\f[B]\[en]exercism\-dir\f[R] \f[I]PATH\f[R]] [\f[B]\[en]tier\f[R] \f[I]T\f[R]] [\f[B]\[en]dry\-run\f[R]]
Import exercises from a cloned Exercism Python track.
.TP
\f[B]completion\f[R] {\f[B]bash\f[R],\f[B]zsh\f[R]}
Generate a shell completion script.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
\f[B].marathon_user\f[R]
Plain text file in \f[I]exercises/\f[R] containing the user\[cq]s name
(e.g., \f[CR]mitch\f[R]).
Used to namespace progress and answer submission.
Gitignored.
.TP
\f[B].marathon_progress.json\f[R]
JSON progress cache in \f[I]exercises/\f[R].
Per\-user namespaced.
Tracks status, hints used, first\-solved timestamp, solve duration,
SM\-2 scheduling fields, streak, badges, and kata count.
Gitignored.
.TP
\f[B]manifest.json\f[R]
Exercise metadata in \f[I]exercises/\f[R].
Maps exercise IDs to slug, tier, source, tags, difficulty, and target
minutes.
.TP
\f[B]badges.json\f[R]
Badge specifications in \f[I]exercises/\f[R].
Defines 16 achievements with slugs, names, and descriptions.
.SH EXERCISE FORMAT
Each exercise directory contains:
.IP
.EX
NNN_slug/
  README.md           Problem statement
  problem.py          Stub (learner edits this)
  test_problem.py     Pytest tests (read\-only)
  .meta/
    stub.py           Original stub snapshot
    solution.py       Reference solution
    hints.md          3 progressive hints
    notes.md          Why it matters + pitfalls
.EE
